},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9367f1",
"children":[
"Gynecomastia is caused by proliferation of glandular tissues in the male breast because of an increase in the ratio of estrogen to androgen. Diagnosis is confirmed by finding subareolar glandular tissue >0.5 cm in diameter and is usually bilateral. Causes include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fc3180",
"children":[
"medications (spironolactone, cimetidine, antiandrogens, 5Î±-reductase inhibitors, protease inhibitors)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"67b78a",
"children":[
"opioid use"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"98d14e",
"children":[
"cirrhosis, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic kidney disease",
"children":[
"CKD"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f79792",
"children":[
"hypogonadism, hyperthyroidism"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a2b99b",
